During the course the Trainees acquire basic professional language by familiarizing themselves with English terminology used in the Estonian legal system. They practice the terms, related to the Estonian law, in discussions, comments, etc. Attention is paid to paraphrasing and explaining the terms.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to learn legal English with the stress on terminology related to the Estonian legal system, the use of these acquired terms for reading legal texts, in professional conversations and academic presentations. Aimed levels: reading B2, listening and speaking B2, writing B2.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  A student who has passed the course is able to 1. recognize and understand legal terms in the context; 2. find Estonian equivalents in the Internet or the reference books; 3. find and present relevant information to the colleague (using terms) and to the client (including paraphrases) in the form of a discussion or a presentation
